value: Breeds in northern North America south of the Barren Grounds from northwestern Alaska to Labrador, south to the upper Yukon Valley, northern British Columbia, Fort Churchill (probably), Magdalen Islands, Newfoundland and Sable Island. Winters from southern California, Texas and North Carolina south through Mexico, Central America, the West Indies and South America to Peru and eastern Brazil; Galapagos Archipelago.

value: Mossy or wet grassy tundra, occasionally in drier areas with scattered scrubby bushes bogs (breeding); marshes, flooded and wet fields, and shores of pools and shallow lakes, occasionally beaches and mudflats (nonbreeding).
